mistral.reason: Cool Night is a song, not the previous work of '65 Love Affair. '65 Love Affair was preceded by Cool Night as a single from Paul Davis's album Cool Night.

gemma2.reason: Several passages state that "'65 Love Affair" was released as a single *after* "Cool Night" dropped off the charts.

llama3.1.reason: The claim is wrong because "Cool Night" was the first single from the album of the same name, which was released before "'65 Love Affair". Therefore, "'65 Love Affair" cannot be considered as the previous work of "Cool Night".

qwen2.5.reason: "'65 Love Affair" was the second single from the album "Cool Night," not a previous work of it. Cool Night was the album that contained both "Cool Night" and "’65 Love Affair."
